article.headline: Coppin St 76, San Diego 62
article.story: CINCINNATI (AP) -- Reserve Chad Yates scored 18 points to lead Coppin State to a 76-62 win over San Diego on Monday in the Black Coaches Association Classic. Substitute Darryl Jones added 14 points and Jimmy Boykin had 11 for the Eagles (1-2), who earned their first win outside the Mid-Eastern Athletic Conference since they beat Loyola-Maryland during the 2001-02 season. They lost all 10 nonleague games last season and their first two this season. San Diego's Brice Vounang scored 20 points. The Toreros, the defending West Coast Conference tournament champions, fell to 0-3 for the first time since moving to Division I in the 1979-80 season. Yates, who had a total of 10 points in Coppin State's first two games, scored 14 on 6-of-8 shooting from the field in the first half. He had eight during an 18-7 run that left the Eagles ahead 33-20 with 3:20 left in the half. The Eagles twice led by 22 points in the second half. The eight-team tournament is being played on Xavier's home court. The Musketeers are the top team in the three-day event.
